com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.embedded

Interface IFIXSourceProxy

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterProcessor

    public interface IFIXSourceProxy
    Interface to be implemented be classes capable of sending FIX messages.

    • Method Detail

      • isLoggedOn

        boolean isLoggedOn()
        Return whether the FIX session to which this proxy is attached is logged on or not.

        If the proxy is attached to multiple sessions then the behavior of this method is undefined.

        Callers should be aware that a true return value is not a guarantee that a subsequent fireMessage(IFIXMessage) will succeed or fail. It is always possible that the logged on state of a FIX session changes between this call and any subsequent attempt to send a message.

        Returns:
        True if the FIX session to which this proxy is attached is logged on, false otherwise.

      • fireMessage

        void fireMessage(IFIXMessage message)
          throws Exception
        Fire a message to FIX via this proxy.

        This method has exactly the same semantics as IFIXSource.fireMessage(com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.IFIXMessage).

        The thread safety associated with sending FIX messages depends on how the proxy is configured and whether there are other upstream components in the Catalys Server's message processing pipeline. Therefore thread safety is both configuration and concrete implementation dependent.

        Parameters:
        message - The message to send.
        Throws:
        Exception - On an underlying send error. Callers must expect and be prepared to handle this error regardless of the result of any previous call to isLoggedOn().

      • setAccumulator

        void setAccumulator(IAccumulator accumulator)
        Set the FIX source accumulator which may be used to measure outbound latencies.
        Parameters:
        accumulator - The FIX source accumulator.
